From: dct-quantization project <dct-quantization@local>
Subject: [PATCH 01/XX] ggml.h: add GGML_TYPE_EOQ transport type and GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_EOQ
Date: 2026-03-28

Add the EOQ (Entropy-Optimized Quantization) transport type to the GGML
type system. EOQ is NOT a real quantization type -- it is a transport
compression format that wraps existing quantized tensors with rANS-based
entropy coding for smaller GGUF file sizes.

Design invariants:

  1. GGML_TYPE_EOQ is used ONLY in GGUF files on disk. It tells the
     loader "this tensor blob is rANS-encoded; decode it first."

  2. During model loading, every tensor marked GGML_TYPE_EOQ must be
     decoded (rANS decompress -> recover original quant blocks) and its
     type changed back to the original (e.g. Q4_K, Q6_K, Q8_0, etc.).
     The original type is stored in the EOQ block header.

  3. After loading completes, NO tensor in memory may have type
     GGML_TYPE_EOQ. If any remain, it is a loader bug.

  4. No compute kernels (vec_dot, mul_mat, etc.) exist for EOQ.
     The type_traits entry has is_quantized=false, blck_size=1,
     type_size=1, and null function pointers (see 02_ggml_c.patch).
     This ensures any accidental use at runtime triggers an immediate
     assertion failure rather than silent corruption.

GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_EOQ follows the same pattern -- it signals that the
GGUF file predominantly contains EOQ-wrapped tensors. After loading,
the effective ftype is determined by the original types recovered from
the EOQ containers.

---
 ggml/include/ggml.h | 14 +++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

NOTE: This is a descriptive patch. The exact line numbers depend on the
version of llama.cpp you are patching against. The context lines show
the surrounding code to locate each hunk. Adjust offsets as needed for
your checkout. See README.md in this directory for application guidance.

Base reference: ggml-org/llama.cpp post-TurboQuant merge (TBQ3_0=41,
TBQ4_0=42, GGML_TYPE_COUNT=43).

================================================================================
HUNK 1: enum ggml_type -- add GGML_TYPE_EOQ, bump GGML_TYPE_COUNT
================================================================================

diff --git a/ggml/include/ggml.h b/ggml/include/ggml.h
index 0000000..1111111 100644
--- a/ggml/include/ggml.h
+++ b/ggml/include/ggml.h
@@ -XXX,7 +XXX,13 @@ enum ggml_type {
         GGML_TYPE_NVFP4   = 40,
         GGML_TYPE_TBQ3_0  = 41,
         GGML_TYPE_TBQ4_0  = 42,
-        GGML_TYPE_COUNT   = 43,
+
+        // EOQ transport compression -- NOT a compute type.
+        // Used only in GGUF files on disk. Tensors are rANS-encoded blocks
+        // that must be decoded to their original quant type during loading.
+        // After loading, no tensor should remain as GGML_TYPE_EOQ.
+        GGML_TYPE_EOQ     = 43,
+
+        GGML_TYPE_COUNT   = 44,
     };

================================================================================
HUNK 2: enum ggml_ftype -- add GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_EOQ
================================================================================

--- a/ggml/include/ggml.h
+++ b/ggml/include/ggml.h
@@ -XXX,6 +XXX,11 @@ enum ggml_ftype {
         GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_IQ4_XS         = 22,
         GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_IQ1_M          = 23,
         GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_BF16           = 24,
+        GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_TQ1_0          = 25, // if not already present
+        GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_TQ2_0          = 26, // if not already present
+
+        // EOQ: file-level flag indicating tensors use entropy-coded transport.
+        // After loading, the real ftype is whatever the decoded tensors use.
+        GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_EOQ            = 29,
     };

--- end of patch ---
